{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T19:07:25Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "lifecycle-and-hook-hygiene-one-offs", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "Intent clarity rated High on the basis that each of the 4 sub-items has its own acceptance signal, but two acceptance signals (auto-scan delete-vs-optimize; skill-edit-advisor replacement shape) describe a decision procedure, not a decision — that is deferred intent, not clarified intent.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness rated High because file paths are enumerated, but the auto-scan deletion path pulls in skills/discovery/SKILL.md and CHANGELOG.md (not listed) and the skill-edit-advisor replacement may modify justfile recipes — bounded file lists that omit downstream-required edits are not bounded.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The Step 2 fix presumes the resolver's filename field carries through all four call sites; the source flags this as a research hook, so the bounded scope claim is contingent on a pending research outcome.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements alignment rated High by citing project.md §23 and §19, but §23 only applies to the auto-scan delete branch — not to the optimize branch and not to the other three sub-items; alignment is per-sub-item and per-branch, not uniform.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Complexity rated complex on the basis of 4 distinct concerns, but two of those concerns are unresolved binary/n-ary design decisions whose outcomes change the implementation surface materially — the ticket is closer to a hygiene fix bundled with 2 scoped discovery sub-tasks.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Criticality rated high on regression surface, but the source's Out of scope explicitly excludes adding new tests; the assessment absorbed this tension silently rather than flagging it.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "The parent epic frames headline findings as token-waste outcomes (~3-15k tok, ~500 tok/feature, ~2,300 tok, ~400 tok